=3D"cm-harlowe-2-inequality cm-harlowe-2-root">&lt;</span></code> symbols c=
ouldn&#39;t be used as operators inside macros, resulting in awkward <code>=
<span class=3D"cm-harlowe-2-error cm-harlowe-2-root">gt</span></code> and <=
code><span class=3D"cm-harlowe-2-error cm-harlowe-2-root">lt</span></code> =
